00:04:56.460 --> 00:04:58.620
It's the gene for
cystic fibrosis.

00:04:58.620 --> 00:05:01.010
It's the gene for obesity.

00:05:01.010 --> 00:05:01.990
No.

00:05:01.990 --> 00:05:05.490
Genes are things that
make things in cells.

00:05:05.490 --> 00:05:08.150
They're basically
cookery recipes.

00:05:08.150 --> 00:05:11.320
So when you're trying to talk
about how our genes work,

00:05:11.320 --> 00:05:12.900
it's always important
to remember,

00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:14.960
genes are instructions
that make things.

00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:17.220
And then it's how those
things in our cells,

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:20.520
in our bodies, in our brains
are all put together and work

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.450
that make us who we are, give
us the abilities and skills

00:05:23.450 --> 00:05:27.000
that we have, and also
the diseases that we get.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:30.750
So I'm going to do a really
tiny bit of molecular biology.

00:05:30.750 --> 00:05:32.890
And I'm going to
apologize, because I'm

00:05:32.890 --> 00:05:34.690
