So please laugh appropriately.

00:05:39.570 --> 00:05:42.310
So I'm going to explain to you
how genes work, and then we

00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:44.430
can all go home.

00:05:44.430 --> 00:05:45.510
Genes work like this.

00:05:45.510 --> 00:05:46.350
You have DNA.

00:05:46.350 --> 00:05:47.880
That's some DNA.

00:05:47.880 --> 00:05:49.110
That's a gene.

00:05:49.110 --> 00:05:51.030
So a gene is basically
an instruction

00:05:51.030 --> 00:05:53.380
that is just a segment of DNA.

00:05:53.380 --> 00:05:55.550
It's kind of a
recipe within a book.

00:05:55.550 --> 00:05:58.670
All the DNA in your cells is
like a recipe book or a recipe

00:05:58.670 --> 00:06:02.780
library, and a gene
is just one recipe.

00:06:02.780 --> 00:06:06.800
This is the thing
that reads the recipe.

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:08.060
It's called RNA polymerase.

00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:11.400
Reads the recipe.
(SINGING) Da da da da da!

00:06:11.400 --> 00:06:14.270
It took me so long to
work out how to do that.

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:17.200
I'm really bad at PowerPoint.

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:21.670
I may even move on to, like,
a star fade at some point.

00:06:21.670 --> 00:06:23.720
And it makes a
molecule called RNA.

00:06:23.720 --> 00:06:26.130
So RNA polymerase makes RNA.

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:29.000
And that is the
message from the gene

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:34.680
that then a cell uses
to build something.

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:37.570
This is the chef that's
making stuff in the cells

00:06:37.570 --> 00:06:40.200
from the copied
instructions in the recipe.

00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:42.520
It's called a ribosome.

00:06:42.520 --> 00:06:49.460
Reads it, makes something,
and it makes protein.

00:06:49.460 --> 00:06:54.520
And proteins are the things
in your cells that do stuff.

00:06:54.520 --> 00:06:57.070
So your skin is kind
of hard and solid

00:06:57.070 --> 00:06:58.930
and keeps the outside
out and the inside

00:06:58.930 --> 00:07:01.700
in because it's full of
a protein called keratin.

00:07:01.700 --> 00:07:03.300
The cells in the
back of your eyeballs

00:07:03.300 --> 00:07:07.040
can see because they have
proteins that can sense light

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:09.410
and can send those
messages to your brain.

00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:12.540
All of our bodies are
made up of proteins.

00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:14.670
Kind of all the
molecules as well.

00:07:14.670 --> 00:07:17.840
But genes are the instructions
that tell your cells

00:07:17.840 --> 00:07:18.990
to make proteins.

00:07:18.990 --> 00:07:20.310
They're recipes.

00:07:20.310 --> 00:07:21.480
So again, just to reiterate.

00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:25.160
Genes are not things that
give you diseases or give you

00:07:25.160 --> 00:07:26.050
traits.

00:07:26.050 --> 00:07:28.280
They make stuff.

00:07:28.280 --> 00:07:30.110
So a little-- a few
facts, because I

00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:32.260
know you all like facts here.

00:07:32.260 --> 00:07:33.040
Factual things.

00:07:33.040 --> 00:07:35.290
So I'll have to keep
it nice and factual.

00:07:35.290 --> 00:07:36.870
My favorite fact
about biology, you

00:07:36.870 --> 00:07:43.430
