00:09:58.930 --> 00:09:59.650
It's just junk.

00:09:59.650 --> 00:10:01.410
It's just there.

00:10:01.410 --> 00:10:04.180
Is it just junk?

00:10:04.180 --> 00:10:05.920
No, it's not.

00:10:05.920 --> 00:10:08.180
So there are all kinds
of things in your genome

00:10:08.180 --> 00:10:12.670
in between the genes that
are-- some of it is junk, true.

00:10:12.670 --> 00:10:15.680
But there are things like
all the control switches that

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:18.430
turn your genes on and
off in the right time

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:24.485
and in the right place to make
you, you, and to make you work.

00:10:24.485 --> 00:10:26.610
There are genes as-- well,
I said at the beginning,

00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:29.674
there are genes that encode the
instructions to make proteins.

00:10:29.674 --> 00:10:32.090
But there's also lots and lots
of genes that are just read

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.240
into that message, that RNA.

00:10:34.240 --> 00:10:36.500
And that does stuff
in cells as well.

00:10:36.500 --> 00:10:38.890
There's a lot we really
don't understand about that,

00:10:38.890 --> 00:10:41.480
but it's a very
interesting area.

00:10:41.480 --> 00:10:44.120
A huge chunk of your
genome-- and I'm

00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:48.570
