00:49:38.770 --> 00:49:39.920
How many control switches--

00:49:39.920 --> 00:49:41.003
MALE SPEAKER: [INAUDIBLE].

00:49:41.003 --> 00:49:41.705
[LAUGHTER]

00:49:41.705 --> 00:49:43.830
KAT ARNEY: How many controls
switches in the genome

00:49:43.830 --> 00:49:47.255
would we have to change to
turn a human into a chimp?

00:49:47.255 --> 00:49:49.115
[SIGH]

00:49:49.900 --> 00:49:54.300
Probably not that many.

00:49:54.300 --> 00:49:58.210
Well-- and we are extremely,
extremely similar.

00:49:58.210 --> 00:50:00.980
And it's probably a few of
the key developmental genes.

00:50:00.980 --> 00:50:05.230
So some of the brain
ones, obviously

00:50:05.230 --> 00:50:08.490
like the hair and face thing.

00:50:08.490 --> 00:50:12.587
The bony penis business.

00:50:12.587 --> 00:50:14.420
Actually, there's a
really interesting story

00:50:14.420 --> 00:50:16.690
that I had to take out of
the book about this woman

00:50:16.690 --> 00:50:19.990
in Stanford who's discovered
that a lot of the switches

00:50:19.990 --> 00:50:23.210
responsible for the shape
of human faces compared

00:50:23.210 --> 00:50:27.720
to chimp faces are derived from
long dead viruses in our DNA.

00:50:27.720 --> 00:50:29.760
So it's like,
literally these viruses

00:50:29.760 --> 00:50:32.430
are the things that have made
us humans compared to chimps.

00:50:32.430 --> 00:50:36.600
So I reckon if you started
knocking out loads of those,

00:50:36.600 --> 00:50:39.530
you would start to get some--
back towards something that

00:50:39.530 --> 00:50:42.875
looked more like a chimp
and less like a human.

00:50:42.875 --> 00:50:45.810
I must publish
that at some point.

00:50:45.810 --> 00:50:46.870
But yeah.

00:50:46.870 --> 00:50:47.661
MALE SPEAKER: Yeah.

00:50:47.661 --> 00:50:49.280
We'll take one more question.

00:50:49.280 --> 00:50:51.925
The gentleman behind there.

00:50:51.925 --> 00:50:54.790
AUDIENCE: Just going back to
the Mendelian diseases, which

00:50:54.790 --> 00:50:58.119
I presume is your
